WEBVTT

00:07.417 --> 00:08.333
UGH.

00:24.250 --> 00:25.667
UHH.

00:25.667 --> 00:26.834
NICE DRAMATIC ENTRANCE.

00:26.834 --> 00:27.583
I AIM TO PLEASE.
THANKS.

00:27.583 --> 00:30.083
WOW...

00:31.083 --> 00:33.500
ARE THESE ALL
THE COLLEGES YOU GOT INTO?

00:33.500 --> 00:36.333
WELL, THE COLLEGES
THAT JACK AND I BOTH
GOT ACCEPTED TO.

00:36.333 --> 00:39.041
NOW, ALL WE HAVE TO DO
IS NARROW DOWN
THE CHOICES.

00:39.041 --> 00:40.333
THERE'S, LIKE,
5 COLLEGES THERE.

00:40.333 --> 00:41.625
WHAT CAN I SAY?

00:41.625 --> 00:43.041
HE'S REALLY GOOD
AT THE APPLICATION
PROCESS,

00:43.041 --> 00:44.875
WHICH MEANS HE CAN
ALWAYS RESORT
TO A CAREER

00:44.875 --> 00:47.375
IN CIVIL SERVICE
OR EDUCATION.

00:47.375 --> 00:49.000
SO, HOW ABOUT YOU?
YOU HEAR ANYTHING?

00:49.000 --> 00:51.333
NO. WHICH MEANS
I CAN ALWAYS RESORT

00:51.333 --> 00:51.708
TO A CAREER IN WAITRESSING.

00:51.708 --> 00:53.542
HARDLY.

00:56.041 --> 00:58.250
Jen: HMM. SOMETHING
TELLS ME YOU'RE WRONG.

01:00.041 --> 01:00.625
SOMETHING TELLS ME
IT'S A SIGN.

01:00.625 --> 01:02.708
YOU THINK?

01:02.708 --> 01:03.875
WELL, WOULD THERE
BE ANOTHER REASON

01:03.875 --> 01:06.417
TO PULL
THE RESPECTABLE
DAWSON LEERY

01:06.417 --> 01:08.500
OUT OF CLASS?
I THINK NOT.

01:16.250 --> 01:19.041
HEY. THIS IS
A COINCIDENCE.

01:19.041 --> 01:20.291
HOPEFULLY A GOOD ONE.

01:20.291 --> 01:22.959
I'LL BE GLAD
WHEN APRIL'S OVER.

01:22.959 --> 01:24.291
PARENTS SHOULD
LET YOU KIDS

01:24.291 --> 01:25.667
OPEN YOUR OWN COLLEGE MAIL

01:25.667 --> 01:28.125
INSTEAD OF TORTURING YOU
OVER THE PHONE.

01:28.125 --> 01:30.542
DIAL 9 TO GET OUT.

01:32.125 --> 01:34.959
WELL, I GUESS
THIS IS IT.

01:34.959 --> 01:37.000
ANOTHER
LIFE-ALTERING MOMENT.

01:38.583 --> 01:39.917
GOOD LUCK.

01:39.917 --> 01:41.583
SAME TO YOU.

01:45.250 --> 01:50.917
MOM. HEY. YEAH,
THAT'S WHY I CALLED.

01:50.917 --> 01:51.959
N.Y.U. FILM? OPEN IT.

01:51.959 --> 01:55.250
HEY, BESSIE.
NO, I'M GLAD THAT YOU CALLED.

01:55.250 --> 01:56.583
FINALLY CAME.

01:56.583 --> 01:58.125
WELL, I DON'T THINK
I CAN WAIT TILL I GET HOME.

01:58.125 --> 01:59.125
DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN READ IT TO ME?

01:59.125 --> 02:00.125
MOM, COULD YOU
READ THAT AGAIN?

02:00.125 --> 02:01.917
I DON'T THINK
I UNDERSTOOD.

02:01.917 --> 02:05.375
NO, IT DOESN'T.
IT REALLY SAYS THAT?

02:05.375 --> 02:06.875
OH, MY GOD.

02:06.875 --> 02:08.667
YEAH. NO, I HEARD YOU.

02:08.667 --> 02:09.834
YEAH.

02:09.834 --> 02:12.542
I UNDERSTAND.

02:13.125 --> 02:15.250
ALL RIGHT. GOTTA GO.

03:11.667 --> 03:13.792
ARE YOU SURE THERE'S
NOTHING I CAN DO?

03:13.792 --> 03:15.000
JOEY, STOP IT. I'M OK.

03:15.000 --> 03:16.959
WELL, IT'S JUST
IF THE CIRCUMSTANCES
WERE REVERSED,

03:16.959 --> 03:17.959
I KNOW HOW I'D FEEL.

03:17.959 --> 03:20.333
YOU'D BE HAPPY FOR ME,
LIKE I AM FOR YOU.

03:22.708 --> 03:24.542
HEY, WHAT'S UP,
CAMPERS?

03:27.166 --> 03:29.000
OK, WE GOT
SOME WEIRD CHI
GOING ON HERE.

03:29.000 --> 03:30.166
YEAH, WELL I'LL LET HER
GIVE YOU THE GOOD NEWS.

03:30.166 --> 03:32.458
I GOTTA GET TO CLASS.
PROMISE ME YOU'LL CELEBRATE.

03:34.041 --> 03:35.917
SO, WHAT'S
THE GOOD NEWS?

03:35.917 --> 03:37.083
WELL, WE BOTH
JUST CALLED HOME,

03:37.083 --> 03:39.250
AND WHILE HE FOUND OUT
HE GOT REJECTED BY N.Y.U.,

03:39.250 --> 03:41.542
I FOUND OUT THAT I GOT

03:41.542 --> 03:42.333
ACCEPTED TO WORTHY.

03:42.333 --> 03:45.083
WORTHINGTON.
OH, YOU GOT IN!

03:45.083 --> 03:47.041
HA HA HA!
CONGRATULATIONS,
SWEETHEART.

03:47.041 --> 03:48.792
THIS IS
FANTASTIC NEWS.

03:50.500 --> 03:52.375
OH, COME ON. BE HAPPY.
YOU HEARD THE MAN.

03:52.375 --> 03:55.041
YOU GOT NOTHING TO FEEL
GUILTY ABOUT HERE.

03:55.041 --> 03:56.125
WELL, IT'S JUST
SO SURREAL.

03:56.125 --> 03:57.708
I MEAN, STUFF LIKE THIS
DOESN'T HAPPEN TO ME.

03:57.708 --> 04:00.208
COME ON.

04:00.208 --> 04:03.333
WHERE ARE WE GOING?
WE STILL HAVE
SIXTH PERIOD.

04:03.333 --> 04:04.750
WELL, WITH ALL DUE RESPECT

04:04.750 --> 04:05.875
TO MR. RINGLER'S
HISTORY CLASS,

04:05.875 --> 04:07.333
TODAY IS ABOUT THE FUTURE,
YOUR FUTURE.

04:07.333 --> 04:08.333
AND I HAVE
THIS FUNNY FEELING

04:08.333 --> 04:09.417
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
BELIEVE THAT LETTER

04:09.417 --> 04:10.375
UNTIL YOU SEE IT.

04:10.375 --> 04:12.250
PACEY, I CAN'T
JUST CUT CLASS.

04:12.250 --> 04:14.083
OH, YOU'RE NOT GONNA
GET INTO COLLEGE?

04:14.083 --> 04:15.333
PLEASE.

04:22.417 --> 04:23.917
NO.

04:23.917 --> 04:26.291
NO, NO, NO, NO.
I'M NOT WATCHING
THAT VIDEO AGAIN, JEN.

04:26.291 --> 04:28.834
IT'S TOO HANDHELD.
IT'S GONNA MAKE ME HURL.

04:28.834 --> 04:32.083
BUT I DO LIKE
THE ONE WITH
THE QUEENY PROFESSOR

04:32.083 --> 04:34.166
THAT'S TALKING ABOUT
THE HISTORY OF
THE STATUE OF LIBERTY.

04:34.166 --> 04:35.625
YOU LAUGHED
THROUGH THE WHOLE THING.

04:35.625 --> 04:36.834
JACK, COME ON, BE SERIOUS.

04:36.834 --> 04:38.083
ALL RIGHT.

04:38.083 --> 04:39.583
WE'VE GOT A LOT
OF SCHOOLS TO COVER,

04:39.583 --> 04:40.750
AND WE NEED TO MAKE
AN INFORMED DECISION HERE,

04:40.750 --> 04:42.542
SO...

04:42.542 --> 04:44.208
OK. SO, WHY DON'T WE
DO THIS SYSTEMATICALLY?

04:44.208 --> 04:45.625
JEN, I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY WE'RE WASTING
OUR TIME WITH THIS.

04:45.625 --> 04:47.917
WE BOTH KNOW THERE IS
ONLY ONE CHOICE, RIGHT?

04:47.917 --> 04:49.917
THE UNIVERSITY
OF NEW YORK.

04:49.917 --> 04:51.542
WHAT?
IT'S A GREAT SCHOOL,

04:51.542 --> 04:52.458
AND YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT'S ALWAYS SAYING
THAT NEW YORK

04:52.458 --> 04:54.458
IS THE ONLY CITY
WORTH LIVING IN.

04:54.458 --> 04:56.458
SO, PLEASE CAN WE
JUST DO THIS?

04:56.458 --> 05:00.792
WELL, WHAT WOULD YOU SAY
IF I SAID THAT I...

05:00.792 --> 05:02.667
THAT I WASN'T
SO SURE ANYMORE?

05:02.667 --> 05:04.834
I'D SAY...

05:04.834 --> 05:06.959
SOMEONE NEEDS TO DEAL
WITH THEIR ISSUES.

05:09.625 --> 05:10.625
20 POUNDS OF CHICKEN,

05:10.625 --> 05:13.792
FRESH ROSEMARY,
HONEY, ORANGE JUICE--

05:13.792 --> 05:15.959
BODIE, SLOW DOWN.
YOU'RE TALKING TOO FAST.

05:15.959 --> 05:17.458
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
DOING?

05:17.458 --> 05:21.542
JO, I AM SO PROUD
OF YOU.

05:21.542 --> 05:23.125
AND MOM WOULD BE,
TOO.

05:23.125 --> 05:24.291
DO I GET A HUG
FROM THE COLLEGE GIRL?

05:26.000 --> 05:27.041
HEY, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HOME SO EARLY?

05:27.041 --> 05:28.959
Pacey: WELL, SHE'S
HAVING A BIT OF TROUBLE

05:28.959 --> 05:30.625
WITH THE BELIEVING PART.

05:30.625 --> 05:32.208
YOU WOULDN'T HAPPEN
TO HAVE A CERTAIN LETTER
HANDY, WOULD YOU?

05:32.208 --> 05:34.667
I THINK I CAN
DIG THAT UP.

05:34.667 --> 05:35.834
SO, UH...

05:35.834 --> 05:37.959
DID WE INTERRUPT
SOMETHING?

05:37.959 --> 05:40.291
ONLY THE BARBECUE
WE'RE PLANNING FOR TOMORROW

05:40.291 --> 05:42.542
TO CELEBRATE THE FIRST POTTER
TO GET INTO COLLEGE.

05:42.542 --> 05:45.041
COULD I ACTUALLY BE
MORE EXCITED THAN YOU ARE?

05:45.041 --> 05:46.083
NOT POSSIBLE.

05:46.083 --> 05:47.625
OK, THEN.

05:47.625 --> 05:50.125
SO, WHO DO YOU
WANT TO INVITE?

05:50.125 --> 05:52.333
YOU'RE REALLY SERIOUS.

05:52.333 --> 05:53.667
IT'S NOT EVERY DAY
THAT A POTTER

05:53.667 --> 05:54.750
GETS ACCEPTED TO ONE
OF THE MOST

05:54.750 --> 05:56.834
PRESTIGIOUS COLLEGES
IN THE COUNTRY.

05:56.834 --> 05:58.875
OR ANY COLLEGE
FOR THAT MATTER.

06:05.792 --> 06:08.125
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU
WAITING FOR?

06:08.125 --> 06:09.250
WELL, BESSIE ALREADY
READ IT TO ME.

06:09.250 --> 06:11.458
I KNOW WHAT IT SAYS
ALREADY.

06:11.458 --> 06:13.542
DON'T KNOW WHY
I'M SO NERVOUS.

06:13.542 --> 06:17.542
YOU'RE NERVOUS BECAUSE
THIS MAKES IT REAL.

06:20.959 --> 06:23.208
[CLEARS THROAT]

06:23.208 --> 06:25.667
"DEAR
JOSEPHINE POTTER..."

06:27.041 --> 06:29.708
"CONGRATULATIONS.

06:29.708 --> 06:32.166
"WORTHINGTON COLLEGE
IS PLEASED TO OFFER YOU

06:32.166 --> 06:35.542
ADMITTANCE FOR THE FALL
SEMESTER OF 2001."

06:41.125 --> 06:42.542
[KNOCKING]

06:42.542 --> 06:43.750
Dawson: I GOT IT.

06:45.875 --> 06:47.542
I SAID I'VE GOT IT.

06:47.542 --> 06:49.166
YOU SHOULDN'T BE RUNNING
AROUND ANSWERING DOORS

06:49.166 --> 06:52.166
ANYWAY IN YOUR CONDITION.
RELAX. GO KNIT SOMETHING.

06:52.166 --> 06:54.708
AND STOP GIVING ME
THE PITYING-MOM LOOK,

06:54.708 --> 06:56.125
LIKE THE WORST THING
IN THE WORLD

06:56.125 --> 06:57.333
HAS HAPPENED TO ME.
IT'S ONE SCHOOL.

06:57.333 --> 06:59.250
HONEY, I JUST WISH THERE
WAS SOMETHING I COULD DO

06:59.250 --> 07:01.083
TO TAKE THE STING OFF
THE DISAPPOINTMENT.

07:01.083 --> 07:03.125
MOM, I'M FINE.

07:03.125 --> 07:04.708
REALLY.

07:06.542 --> 07:07.708
HEY.
HEY.

07:07.708 --> 07:08.750
HEY.

07:11.208 --> 07:15.250
HI, GALE.
HI.

07:15.250 --> 07:16.417
I'M GLAD THE TWO OF YOU
ARE GOING OUT.

07:16.417 --> 07:17.625
HE NEEDS TO GET HIS MIND--

07:17.625 --> 07:19.625
GOD, MOM. JUST STOP IT.
YOU'RE KILLING ME HERE.

07:21.917 --> 07:23.625
OK.

07:24.625 --> 07:25.667
[SMALL GROAN]

07:25.667 --> 07:29.166
SO, HOW ARE YOU
HOLDING UP?
HONESTLY?

07:34.750 --> 07:36.291
THE TRUTH? IT SUCKS.

07:36.291 --> 07:39.333
IT ABSOLUTELY SUCKS.

07:39.333 --> 07:40.667
I MEAN, IF N.Y.U.
DOESN'T WANT ME,

07:40.667 --> 07:41.458
U.S.C.'s DEFINITELY
NOT GONNA WANT ME,

07:41.458 --> 07:43.333
AND WHERE DOES
THAT LEAVE ME?

07:43.333 --> 07:45.625
WHOA. NO.
FIRST OF ALL,

07:45.625 --> 07:47.834
N.Y.U. HAS NO BEARING
ON U.S.C.

07:47.834 --> 07:48.917
REMEMBER THAT.

07:48.917 --> 07:51.041
AND SECONDLY,
I'D LIKE TO POINT OUT

07:51.041 --> 07:54.208
THAT A CERTAIN
A.I. BROOKS DIDN'T
GO TO FILM SCHOOL.

07:54.208 --> 07:57.125
HE PREFERRED LIFE
AS A TEACHER.

07:57.125 --> 07:59.625
YOU'RE SAYING I COULD
USE THE MONEY HE GAVE ME

07:59.625 --> 08:00.125
TO MAKE MY OWN MOVIES?

08:00.125 --> 08:02.458
WHY NOT?

08:02.458 --> 08:03.291
I MEAN, FILM SCHOOL
DOESN'T HAVE TO BE

08:03.291 --> 08:04.708
THE BE-ALL, END-ALL.

08:07.083 --> 08:08.917
WHAT?

08:10.667 --> 08:13.125
10 MINUTES AGO, I WAS
FEELING COMPLETELY LOST.

08:13.125 --> 08:14.542
I MEAN, JACK AND JEN
GOT INTO JUST ABOUT

08:14.542 --> 08:16.458
EVERYWHERE THEY APPLIED,
JOEY GOT INTO WORTHINGTON,

08:16.458 --> 08:18.417
AND ALL I WANTED
TO DO WAS WALLOW.

08:18.417 --> 08:20.375
BUT THEN SOMEBODY
REMINDED ME THAT THE WORLD

08:20.375 --> 08:23.291
IS FULL OF POSSIBILITIES.

08:33.166 --> 08:34.667
[SIGHS]

08:34.667 --> 08:36.833
YOU AND THAT COUCH
HAVE ALWAYS

08:36.833 --> 08:39.166
GOTTEN ALONG WELL
IN THE PAST.

08:39.166 --> 08:40.166
YOU WANT TO TALK
ABOUT IT?

08:40.166 --> 08:43.625
I'M HAVING A PROBLEM
WITH JACK. UM...

08:43.625 --> 08:45.166
YOU SEE, WE BOTH WANT
TO GO TO THE SAME COLLEGE

08:45.166 --> 08:46.542
OR AT LEAST BE
IN THE SAME CITY

08:46.542 --> 08:48.583
AND HELP EACH OTHER
THROUGH FRESHMAN
ANGST AND ALL.

08:48.583 --> 08:49.667
SOUNDS LIKE A PLAN.

08:49.667 --> 08:50.917
A SUPPORT SYSTEM'S
ALWAYS GOOD,

08:50.917 --> 08:52.834
ESPECIALLY IF YOU'RE
IN FOREIGN SURROUNDINGS.

08:52.834 --> 08:55.000
SEE, THAT'S THE POINT.
THEY WOULDN'T BE FOREIGN

08:55.000 --> 08:56.917
IF WE GO WHERE
HE WANTS TO GO.

08:56.917 --> 08:59.166
WHICH IS WHERE?

08:59.166 --> 09:00.291
NEW YORK CITY.

09:00.291 --> 09:03.500
WHICH BRINGS US BACK

09:03.500 --> 09:04.166
TO YOUR
LEAST FAVORITE TOPIC.

09:04.166 --> 09:07.041
MY PARENTS?

09:07.041 --> 09:08.250
WHY DO YOU THINK, JEN,

09:08.250 --> 09:10.750
THAT THEY KEEP
FINDING THEIR WAY
INTO THIS ROOM?

09:10.750 --> 09:12.708
THAT SOUNDS SUSPICIOUSLY
LIKE A QUESTION

09:12.708 --> 09:14.000
YOU ALREADY KNOW
THE ANSWER TO.

09:14.000 --> 09:15.000
I THINK YOU DO, ALSO.

09:15.000 --> 09:17.208
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE VERY PUSHY TODAY.

09:17.208 --> 09:19.125
IT'S WEDNESDAY.
I'M KINDA PUSHY
ON WEDNESDAYS.

09:19.125 --> 09:20.375
FRIDAYS,
I'M NOT SO PUSHY.

09:20.375 --> 09:22.417
YOU'RE TRYING TO MAKE ME
LAUGH, AREN'T YOU?

09:22.417 --> 09:24.750
I'M TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

09:24.750 --> 09:27.917
WHY YOU DON'T TALK
ABOUT YOUR PARENTS

09:27.917 --> 09:30.500
WITH THE SAME
WRY SENSE OF HUMOR

09:30.500 --> 09:33.208
YOU SEEM TO APPLY
TO EVERY OTHER TOPIC.

09:35.250 --> 09:36.208
WHY?

09:36.208 --> 09:37.083
BECAUSE MAYBE
THEN WE'LL GET

09:37.083 --> 09:39.166
SOME REAL ANSWERS
IN HERE.

09:41.583 --> 09:43.500
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU ACTUALLY TALKED TO THEM?

09:44.875 --> 09:48.125
MY MOM CAME DOWN
LAST THANKSGIVING...

09:48.125 --> 09:50.208
IN A PATHETIC ATTEMPT
TO RESUSCITATE

09:50.208 --> 09:51.291
OUR RELATIONSHIP.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.750
AND YOUR FATHER?

09:53.750 --> 09:57.250
I DON'T KNOW. UM...

09:57.250 --> 09:59.583
I DON'T KNOW.
UM...

09:59.583 --> 10:01.125
GOD. I MEAN, IT'S NOT LIKE
I EVER REALLY TALKED

10:01.125 --> 10:02.250
TO THE MAN
IN THE FIRST PLACE.

10:02.250 --> 10:03.291
HE JUST SORT OF...

10:03.291 --> 10:07.000
HE JUST KINDA TALKS
AT YOU OR, UM...

10:07.000 --> 10:08.792
THROUGH YOU OR AROUND YOU.

10:08.792 --> 10:09.875
TRY TO REMEMBER, JEN.

10:11.583 --> 10:12.458
THIS IS STUPID.

10:12.458 --> 10:14.375
PRETEND LIKE IT'S NOT.
FOR ME.

10:14.375 --> 10:15.458
WHY? SO, THEN YOU'LL
TELL ME THE POINT

10:15.458 --> 10:17.083
OF REMEMBERING
SOME RIDICULOUS CONVERSATION

10:17.083 --> 10:18.458
THAT OBVIOUSLY MEANT
NOTHING TO ME AT THE TIME.

10:18.458 --> 10:21.333
PERHAPS IT DID
MEAN NOTHING TO YOU
AT THE TIME,

10:21.333 --> 10:23.834
BUT OBVIOUSLY IT MEANS
A GREAT DEAL TO YOU NOW.

10:23.834 --> 10:26.333
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I WANT TO LEAVE.

10:26.333 --> 10:28.750
DO YOU?

10:28.750 --> 10:29.625
OR DO YOU WANT TO STAY
AND FIND OUT

10:29.625 --> 10:32.291
WHY THIS IS SO HARD
FOR YOU?

10:37.333 --> 10:39.708
YOU KNOW, BODIE'S GOTTA
STOP BUYING IN BULK.

10:39.708 --> 10:42.291
YOU GOT 11 PEOPLE
COMING OVER.

10:42.291 --> 10:43.291
WE GOT ENOUGH
CHARCOAL HERE

10:43.291 --> 10:45.708
TO BARBECUE
THROUGH LABOR DAY.

10:45.708 --> 10:46.667
YOU WANT SOME HELP?

10:46.667 --> 10:49.708
AND RISK MY BUMBLING
SUPERHERO STATUS?

10:49.708 --> 10:49.959
NO, THANK YOU.

10:53.208 --> 10:55.125
PACE...

10:55.125 --> 10:56.917
LOOK.

10:56.917 --> 11:00.333
I KNOW THAT WE HAVEN'T
REALLY DISCUSSED US YET.

11:00.333 --> 11:03.500
I'M STILL TRYING TO PROCESS
THIS WHOLE COLLEGE THING.

11:03.500 --> 11:04.458
YOU KNOW, IT'S...

11:04.458 --> 11:06.917
KINDA WEIRD
TO GET YOUR DREAM.

11:06.917 --> 11:09.333
I KNOW IT.
I SAY THAT EVERY TIME
I LOOK AT YOU.

11:09.333 --> 11:12.208
YOU ALWAYS DO THAT.
YOU CHANGE THE SUBJECT.

11:12.208 --> 11:14.542
JOEY, WE'RE NOT TALKING
ABOUT THIS TODAY,

11:14.542 --> 11:16.375
BECAUSE WE'RE
NOT TALKING ABOUT
ANYTHING NEGATIVE TODAY,

11:16.375 --> 11:18.333
BECAUSE TODAY IS
YOUR DAY TO CELEBRATE

11:18.333 --> 11:19.750
THIS MOST AMAZING
ACCOMPLISHMENT

11:19.750 --> 11:22.917
THAT YOU HAVE WORKED
SO HARD FOR.

11:22.917 --> 11:24.208
OK. I'M GONNA GO
TO THE GARAGE

11:24.208 --> 11:25.417
AND GET A DOLLY
BEFORE I GIVE MYSELF
A HERNIA.

11:25.417 --> 11:27.583
SO, I'LL SEE YOU INSIDE.

11:52.917 --> 11:58.041
YOU'RE BACK. IT LOOKS
LIKE EVERYONE RSVPed.

11:58.041 --> 12:00.583
JO, WHAT'S WRONG?

12:00.583 --> 12:02.875
I GOT THE FINANCIAL AID
PACKAGE.

12:02.875 --> 12:05.041
AND? HOW MUCH
IS A FULL RIDE?

12:05.041 --> 12:06.875
I WOULDN'T KNOW.

12:06.875 --> 12:09.208
ACCORDING TO THIS,

12:09.208 --> 12:10.875
WORTHINGTON IS HAPPY
TO HAVE ME

12:10.875 --> 12:13.542
SO LONG AS MY PARENTS
KICK IN $15,000.

12:13.542 --> 12:15.375
$15,000?!
THAT CAN'T BE RIGHT.

12:15.375 --> 12:16.917
WE DON'T HAVE
THAT KIND OF MONEY.

12:16.917 --> 12:18.125
I KNOW THAT.

12:22.291 --> 12:25.250
I KNEW THIS WAS
TOO GOOD TO BE TRUE.

12:25.250 --> 12:26.583
IT'S THE UNIVERSE'S WAY
OF SAYING,

12:26.583 --> 12:28.583
"JOEY POTTER, NOT SO FAST.

12:28.583 --> 12:33.625
YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE."

12:37.041 --> 12:39.417
SO, WHAT YOU'RE SAYING IS
THAT WE'RE BEING PENALIZED

12:39.417 --> 12:42.375
BECAUSE OUR FAMILY BUSINESS
IS ACTUALLY MAKING MONEY.

12:42.375 --> 12:44.750
IF IT WEREN'T, THEN WE
WOULD QUALIFY FOR MORE AID.

12:44.750 --> 12:46.125
UNFORTUNATELY, YES.

12:46.125 --> 12:47.083
WE TURNED A PROFIT
FOR THE FIRST TIME,

12:47.083 --> 12:49.250
BUT IT WASN'T LIKE
WE WON THE LOTTERY.

12:49.250 --> 12:50.458
BUT YOU MADE
SUBSTANTIALLY MORE

12:50.458 --> 12:51.583
THAN YOUR 1999 RETURN.

12:51.583 --> 12:53.250
YEAH, BUT WE HAVE MORE DEBT
THAN WE DID IN 1999.

12:53.250 --> 12:56.083
I MEAN, IT COSTS A LOT
OF MONEY TO OPEN A B AND B.

12:56.083 --> 12:58.333
HOW CAN THEY THINK
THAT WE CAN AFFORD $15,000?

12:58.333 --> 12:59.834
BASED ON ONE YEAR'S INCOME?

12:59.834 --> 13:02.458
I DIDN'T SAY THAT
THE SYSTEM WAS FAIR, JOEY.

13:04.250 --> 13:07.041
THIS IS UNBELIEVABLE.
I...

13:09.083 --> 13:10.625
SHOULD'VE APPLIED
FOR MORE SCHOLARSHIPS,

13:10.625 --> 13:11.875
BUT IT'S TOO LATE NOW.

13:11.875 --> 13:14.375
LOOK, I KNOW THAT WE'VE TALKED
ABOUT HIS BEFORE, JOEY,

13:14.375 --> 13:16.500
BUT THERE ARE STUDENT LOANS.

13:16.500 --> 13:18.542
NEARLY EVERYONE THESE DAYS
BORROWS SOME MONEY

13:18.542 --> 13:19.333
TO PAY FOR COLLEGE.

13:19.333 --> 13:20.125
NO, I DON'T WANT
TO GRADUATE

13:20.125 --> 13:21.458
AND BE OVER $60,000
IN DEBT.

13:21.458 --> 13:24.125
I CAN'T START OFF
MY LIFE THAT WAY.
I WON'T.

13:24.125 --> 13:26.542
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

13:26.542 --> 13:27.708
THERE ARE PLENTY
OF OTHER PLACES

13:27.708 --> 13:28.667
I'M WAITING
TO HEAR FROM.

13:28.667 --> 13:30.291
Bessie: BUT THIS IS
YOUR DREAM, JOEY.

13:30.291 --> 13:32.166
BESSIE...

13:32.166 --> 13:35.458
SOMETIMES DREAMS
DON'T ALWAYS COME TRUE.

13:35.458 --> 13:36.667
THANK YOU FOR YOUR TIME.

13:48.291 --> 13:50.458
THE BARBECUE?
THAT'S THE LAST
THING YOU NEED.

13:50.458 --> 13:51.291
I'LL SEND EVERYONE
HOME.

13:51.291 --> 13:53.792
NO.

13:53.792 --> 13:56.208
LOOK, YOU'RE NOT
SENDING THEM ANYWHERE.

13:56.208 --> 13:58.250
JO--

13:58.250 --> 13:59.750
AND YOU'RE NOT TELLING THEM
ANYTHING, BESSIE.

13:59.750 --> 14:03.750
I'M SERIOUS. NOT A WORD.

14:09.834 --> 14:11.708
HEY, THERE, STRANGER.
I WAS STARTING TO THINK

14:11.708 --> 14:13.834
YOU MIGHT MISS
YOUR OWN PARTY.

14:13.834 --> 14:15.041
NO SUCH LUCK.

14:15.375 --> 14:17.250
HUH?

14:17.250 --> 14:19.166
HEY, DAWSON.
HEY, BESSIE.

14:19.166 --> 14:20.208
WHY DON'T I TAKE
THAT FROM YOU?

14:20.208 --> 14:22.125
I'M GOING IN
ANYWAY.

14:22.125 --> 14:24.208
OH, THANKS.

14:24.208 --> 14:25.333
SO, WHERE IS EVERYBODY?

14:25.333 --> 14:27.000
THEY'RE OUT BACK.
GRETCHEN GOT DRAGGED

14:27.000 --> 14:28.417
INTO THE WHOLE
NEW YORK DEBATE.

14:28.417 --> 14:30.333
I WOULD'VE JUMPED IN,
BUT, YOU KNOW,

14:30.333 --> 14:32.500
SINCE NEW YORK
DIDN'T WANT TO HAVE
ANYTHING TO DO WITH ME...

14:33.500 --> 14:36.625
JOEY, THAT WAS
A SELF-DEPRECATING ASIDE.

14:36.625 --> 14:37.708
YOU'RE STILL DOING IT.
DOING WHAT?

14:37.708 --> 14:39.667
ACTING WEIRD AROUND ME.

14:39.667 --> 14:41.708
YOU'VE NO REASON
TO NOT BE HAPPY RIGHT NOW.

14:43.000 --> 14:44.458
I KNOW.

14:44.458 --> 14:45.375
HOW'D IT GO WITH MS. WATSON?

14:45.375 --> 14:46.875
PACEY SAID SOMETHING
ABOUT A MIX-UP.

14:46.875 --> 14:48.542
OH, IT WAS NOTHING.
IT WAS...

14:48.542 --> 14:50.542
IT WAS GREAT.

14:50.542 --> 14:51.542
YOU KNOW, I'M GONNA
GO INSIDE

14:51.542 --> 14:52.708
AND SEE IF THEY
NEED ANY HELP,

14:52.708 --> 14:53.542
AND I'LL MEET
YOU GUYS OUT BACK.

14:53.542 --> 14:55.834
SURE THING.

14:59.500 --> 15:02.208
HEY...

15:02.208 --> 15:03.708
HOW'D IT GO?

15:06.375 --> 15:07.875
OH, IT WAS THAT GOOD, HUH?

15:10.041 --> 15:12.333
BESSIE DIDN'T TELL YOU
THE CRUEL IRONY?

15:14.458 --> 15:16.125
THIS PLACE IS MAKING
TOO MUCH MONEY,

15:16.125 --> 15:16.792
SO I'M SCREWED.

15:16.792 --> 15:20.917
WELL, THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

15:20.917 --> 15:23.417
THERE'S GOTTA BE SOMETHING
YOU CAN DO ABOUT THAT.

15:23.417 --> 15:25.542
THERE'S NOTHING
TO BE DONE.

15:25.542 --> 15:27.458
EXCEPT GO OUT THERE
AND CELEBRATE

15:27.458 --> 15:28.250
THIS AMAZING
ACCOMPLISHMENT

15:28.250 --> 15:30.792
THAT I WORKED
SO HARD FOR.

15:30.792 --> 15:32.125
HEY, HOLD ON A SECOND, JO.

15:32.125 --> 15:33.208
WHY?

15:33.208 --> 15:35.375
PACEY, THERE'S NOTHING
THAT YOU CAN SAY OR DO

15:35.375 --> 15:36.417
THAT CAN CHANGE
WHAT HAPPENED.

15:36.417 --> 15:40.083
IT IS WHAT IT IS.
NO ONE CAN CHANGE THAT.

15:40.083 --> 15:41.583
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
GONNA TELL ALL THEM?

15:41.583 --> 15:43.041
NOTHING.

15:43.041 --> 15:45.041
LOOK, I DON'T WANT ANYONE
TO FEEL SORRY FOR ME, OK?

15:52.917 --> 15:53.750
PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION,
COME ON!

15:53.750 --> 15:55.125
ADMIT THAT'S A HUGE PLUS.

15:55.125 --> 15:57.458
YEAH, SPOKEN LIKE
SOMEBODY WHO'S NEVER

15:57.458 --> 15:58.750
BEEN GROPED ON
THE SUBWAY BEFORE.

15:58.750 --> 16:00.041
I HATE NEW YORK.

16:00.041 --> 16:02.333
AH, SPOKEN LIKE
A VERY LOYAL GIRLFRIEND.

16:02.333 --> 16:03.834
OH, THIS IS
UNBELIEVA...HEY!

16:03.834 --> 16:06.625
THE GUEST
OF HONOR.

16:06.625 --> 16:08.333
GET A DRINK.

16:08.333 --> 16:10.041
ALL RIGHT, I'D LIKE
TO PROPOSE A TOAST.

16:10.041 --> 16:11.250
TO JOEY POTTER,

16:11.250 --> 16:13.417
MAY WORTHINGTON
BE WORTHY OF HER.

16:13.417 --> 16:14.625
[LAUGHS]

16:14.625 --> 16:16.291
Dawson: CHEERS.

16:21.250 --> 16:25.291
SO, YOU'RE JUST IN TIME
TO SETTLE THE DEBATE.

16:25.291 --> 16:27.500
OH, NO, NO. I'M NOT GETTING
IN THE MIDDLE OF THIS.

16:27.500 --> 16:28.583
I SHOULD'VE SAID THAT.

16:28.583 --> 16:30.458
UM...I'M GONNA GO
HELP PACEY.

16:30.458 --> 16:31.875
OTHERWISE THE FOOD
WILL STILL BE ALIVE

16:31.875 --> 16:32.959
WHEN HE SERVES IT.

16:32.959 --> 16:34.000
OK. ALL YOU
HAVE TO DO

16:34.000 --> 16:36.458
IS TELL HIM
THAT NEW YORK SUCKS.

16:36.458 --> 16:39.792
NO, HOLD ON. YOU CANNOT
TELL ME THAT NEW YORK SUCKS.

16:39.792 --> 16:42.792
ESPECIALLY AFTER
TELLING ME HOW GREAT
IT IS FOR 2 YEARS.

16:42.792 --> 16:45.000
WELL, IF I'M
TELLING YOU NOW
THAT IT SUCKS,

16:45.000 --> 16:46.000
SHOULDN'T YOU
LISTEN TO ME?

16:46.000 --> 16:47.417
YOU KNOW, YOU'VE REALLY
GROWN INSENSITIVE

16:47.417 --> 16:48.792
POST YOUR
COLLEGE ACCEPTANCE.

16:48.792 --> 16:49.750
INSENSITIVE TO WHAT?

16:49.750 --> 16:51.708
TO ME AND MY...
MY...

16:51.708 --> 16:53.834
MY SENSITIVITIES.

16:53.834 --> 16:55.750
SENSITIVITIES?
ARE YOU GUYS CATCHING THIS?

16:55.750 --> 16:58.000
OK, THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT--

16:58.000 --> 16:59.333
MAKING FUN OF ME
IN FRONT OF EVERYBODY.

16:59.333 --> 17:00.375
YOU NEVER USED
TO DO THAT.

17:00.375 --> 17:01.583
YEAH, WELL, YOU NEVER
USED TO ACT

17:01.583 --> 17:02.834
LIKE A LUNATIC, EITHER.

17:02.834 --> 17:04.125
THIS LUNATIC'S GETTING
A BURGER.

17:04.125 --> 17:05.333
YOU DON'T EVEN EAT BURGERS.

17:05.333 --> 17:07.834
I SAID I WAS GONNA
GET IT, NOT EAT IT.

17:12.416 --> 17:13.834
YOU OK?

17:13.834 --> 17:14.750
WITH ALL THIS TALK
ABOUT COLLEGE,

17:14.750 --> 17:16.583
I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT FEEL,
WELL...

17:16.583 --> 17:18.250
WELL-DONE?
DON'T WORRY.

17:18.250 --> 17:19.333
I'M VERY AWARE
OF THE HEALTH
HAZARDS

17:19.333 --> 17:21.290
OF COOKING
HAMBURGERS.

17:21.290 --> 17:22.708
YOU'RE NOT GONNA FOOL ME
WITH THAT, PACEY.

17:22.708 --> 17:23.875
WITH WHAT?

17:23.875 --> 17:26.208
WITH THAT PACEY-NESS.

17:26.208 --> 17:28.541
LOOK, I KNOW YOU'RE
HAPPY FOR HER,

17:28.541 --> 17:30.500
BUT IT MAKES
YOU THINK ABOUT
THE FUTURE, RIGHT?

17:30.500 --> 17:32.291
WELL, NO. IT MAKES ME
THINK ABOUT HER FUTURE.

17:32.291 --> 17:33.708
WE DON'T EVEN HAVE
TO THINK ABOUT MY FUTURE,

17:33.708 --> 17:34.875
BECAUSE I DON'T REALLY
HAVE ONE TO THINK OF.

17:34.875 --> 17:36.875
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
THAT BELIEVES THAT,
PACEY,

17:36.875 --> 17:37.917
AND IF YOU KEEP
SAYING IT,

17:37.917 --> 17:39.542
IT'LL HAPPEN.

17:39.542 --> 17:41.291
HAVE YOU THOUGHT
ABOUT WHAT YOU'RE
GONNA DO?

17:41.291 --> 17:43.333
I MEAN, WHAT DO YOU
WANT FOR THE FUTURE?

17:43.333 --> 17:44.500
WHAT DO YOU WANT
FOR THE FUTURE?

17:44.500 --> 17:46.041
SORRY. AS YOUR SISTER,
I RESERVE THE RIGHT

17:46.041 --> 17:48.667
TO PLAY THE
I-ASKED-YOU-FIRST CARD.

17:49.583 --> 17:51.708
HEY, LOOK.
YOU PROMISE NOT TO REPEAT

17:51.708 --> 17:53.458
WHAT I'M ABOUT TO SAY?

17:53.458 --> 17:55.208
YEAH. SURE.
WHAT IS IT?

17:58.000 --> 18:00.959
JOEY'S NOT GOING
TO WORTHINGTON.

18:00.959 --> 18:02.708
THEY DENIED
HER FINANCIAL AID PACKAGE.

18:02.708 --> 18:05.458
SHE'S JUST TOO PROUD
TO TELL ANYBODY ABOUT IT.

18:05.458 --> 18:07.417
THAT'S AWFUL.

18:07.417 --> 18:10.000
YEAH. AND IT GETS
WORSE, ACTUALLY.

18:10.000 --> 18:10.333
HOW CAN IT?

18:12.250 --> 18:14.917
I THINK I'M HAPPY
ABOUT IT.

18:23.583 --> 18:25.291
[SIGHS] OK.

18:26.917 --> 18:29.083
YOU WANNA TELL ME
WHAT THIS IS REALLY ABOUT?

18:29.083 --> 18:30.250
I THINK WE BOTH KNOW
IT'S MORE

18:30.250 --> 18:32.375
THAN MY ALLEGED LACK
OF SENSITIVITY.

18:34.667 --> 18:37.333
YOU KNOW HOW
WHEN YOU MOVED IN
WITH ME AND GRAMS,

18:39.375 --> 18:41.667
YOU SAID THAT YOU
DIDN'T WANT TO GO HOME

18:41.667 --> 18:42.667
BECAUSE YOU DIDN'T
FEEL LIKE

18:42.667 --> 18:44.375
THERE WAS ANYTHING
THERE FOR YOU?

18:44.375 --> 18:44.417
YEAH.

18:46.417 --> 18:50.166
WELL, THAT'S HOW
I FEEL ABOUT NEW YORK.

18:50.166 --> 18:53.041
I KNOW YOU HAVE PROBLEMS
WITH YOUR PARENTS, JEN,

18:53.041 --> 18:54.125
BUT IT'S NOT LIKE
YOU'D BE LIVING WITH THEM.

18:54.125 --> 18:56.166
DON'T LET THAT
STOP YOU FROM GOING.

18:56.166 --> 18:57.458
UHH.

19:01.458 --> 19:03.166
I DON'T KNOW. I WISH
I COULD EXPLAIN THIS TO YOU,

19:03.166 --> 19:07.417
BUT...IT DOESN'T
MAKE ANY SENSE.

19:10.583 --> 19:13.291
I'M AFRAID...

19:16.250 --> 19:18.625
TO GO BACK THERE.

19:18.625 --> 19:21.917
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA
TALK TO FROST ABOUT THIS?

19:21.917 --> 19:24.708
YEAH, HE TRIED.

19:24.708 --> 19:26.959
I JUST CHANGED THE SUBJECT
TO ONE OF MY OTHER NEUROSIS.

19:26.959 --> 19:29.750
WELL, IT'S THERAPY, JEN.

19:29.750 --> 19:30.792
I THINK IT'S LIKE
THE ONE PLACE

19:30.792 --> 19:32.750
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED
TO CHANGE THE SUBJECT.

19:32.750 --> 19:35.875
THEN CAN I CHANGE IT
HERE? PLEASE?

19:39.166 --> 19:42.542
IF YOU DON'T WANNA
GO TO NEW YORK,

19:42.542 --> 19:44.166
WE DON'T HAVE
TO GO TO NEW YORK.

19:44.166 --> 19:45.542
JACK...

19:45.542 --> 19:46.667
NO, IT'S MORE IMPORTANT
TO ME

19:46.667 --> 19:49.125
THAT WE GO
TO SCHOOL TOGETHER.

19:49.125 --> 19:50.333
LOOK, WHATEVER
THIS OLD WOUND OF YOURS IS,

19:50.333 --> 19:54.667
I MEAN, DON'T LET IT
STOP US FROM GOING.

19:54.667 --> 19:55.458
YOU'VE COME TOO FAR
FOR THAT.

19:57.625 --> 20:01.125
NOW, BE A GOOD LITTLE
PSYCHOLOGICALLY
DAMAGED CHILD,

20:01.125 --> 20:04.625
GO BACK TO THERAPY,
AND WORK THIS OUT.

20:04.625 --> 20:06.542
SEE? INSENSITIVE.

20:06.542 --> 20:09.333
OH, COME ON.
I'M KIDDING.

20:09.333 --> 20:12.458
HEY, THERE YOU ARE.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

20:12.458 --> 20:13.834
JOEY,
CONGRATULATIONS.

20:13.834 --> 20:15.959
Gale: HONEY, WE ARE
SO HAPPY FOR YOU.

20:15.959 --> 20:17.083
THANK YOU.

20:17.083 --> 20:19.834
AND YOU.

20:22.708 --> 20:24.875
I THINK YOU'VE BEEN
WAITING FOR THIS.

20:29.875 --> 20:31.250
IT CAME.

20:32.750 --> 20:35.458
IT ACTUALLY CAME.

20:37.333 --> 20:38.542
AREN'T YOU GONNA OPEN IT?

20:38.542 --> 20:41.083
YEAH. IT'S...
[NERVOUS LAUGH]

20:41.083 --> 20:43.542
IT'S A...
IT'S A FAT ENVELOPE.

20:43.542 --> 20:44.333
THAT PAINTS A BETTER PICTURE
THAN YESTERDAY, RIGHT?

20:55.583 --> 20:56.583
I'M IN.

20:56.583 --> 20:59.708
[LAUGHING]

20:59.708 --> 21:01.083
I'M IN!

21:01.083 --> 21:02.250
CONGRATULATIONS.

21:02.250 --> 21:03.959
I CAN'T BELIEVE
IT'S HAPPENING!

21:06.417 --> 21:07.708
Gretchen: IT'S WHAT
YOU ALWAYS WANTED.

21:07.708 --> 21:10.959
COME HERE. OHH!

21:10.959 --> 21:13.792
Mitch: WE ARE SO PROUD
OF YOU, SON.

21:16.375 --> 21:17.583
CONGRATULATIONS,
DAWSON.

21:17.583 --> 21:19.083
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU, MAN.

21:19.083 --> 21:20.417
WHERE'S JOEY?

21:27.708 --> 21:29.875
YOU OK?

21:32.250 --> 21:34.291
OH, YEAH. UM...

21:34.291 --> 21:37.041
CONGRATULATIONS.

21:37.041 --> 21:38.542
CONGRATULATIONS?
JO, YOU'RE A WRECK.

21:40.000 --> 21:42.542
IT'S NOTHING. I'M FINE.

21:42.542 --> 21:46.291
JO, WHATEVER IT IS,
YOU CAN TELL ME.

21:46.291 --> 21:47.625
DAWSON, WE'RE HERE
TO CELEBRATE.

21:47.625 --> 21:50.708
YOU GOT INTO U.S.C.
IT'S WHAT YOU'VE
ALWAYS WANTED.

21:50.708 --> 21:52.458
THAT'S RIGHT,
AND WORTHINGTON
IS WHAT YOU ALWAYS WANTED,

21:52.458 --> 21:53.542
SO WHY DON'T YOU
JUST TELL ME WHAT'S WRONG?

21:53.542 --> 21:56.417
DID YOU NOT GET IN?
DID YOU GET WAIT-LISTED?

22:01.500 --> 22:03.125
I DIDN'T GET THE MONEY.

22:05.458 --> 22:07.542
AT LEAST, I DIDN'T
GET ENOUGH OF IT.

22:08.417 --> 22:11.083
I GOT
MY FINANCIAL AID PACKAGE,

22:11.083 --> 22:15.125
AND EVEN WITH GRANTS
AND WORK-STUDY,

22:16.000 --> 22:16.917
THEY STILL WANT $15,000.

22:17.750 --> 22:18.875
$15,000?

22:18.875 --> 22:21.125
THEY THINK
THAT'S WHAT BESSIE
CAN CONTRIBUTE,

22:21.125 --> 22:22.166
WHICH SHE CAN'T,
SO...

22:22.166 --> 22:23.625
JOEY, THERE'S GOT TO BE
A WAY AROUND THIS.

22:23.625 --> 22:25.834
IT'S JUST MONEY.
YOU CAN'T LET THAT STOP YOU

22:25.834 --> 22:28.542
FROM ACHIEVING SOMETHING
YOU'VE WORKED THIS HARD FOR.

22:28.542 --> 22:31.417
YOU MAKE IT SOUND LIKE
THERE'S SOME EASY ANSWER.

22:31.417 --> 22:33.458
THERE'S GOT TO BE.

22:33.458 --> 22:34.542
THERE'S NOT.

22:35.959 --> 22:37.333
I SPENT HOURS
DOING RESEARCH

22:37.333 --> 22:38.875
EVEN BEFORE I APPLIED,

22:38.875 --> 22:40.583
AND GETTING
THE FINANCIAL AID

22:40.583 --> 22:43.708
WAS AS IMPORTANT
AS ME GETTING ACCEPTED.

22:46.041 --> 22:48.000
IT DIDN'T HAPPEN.

22:49.834 --> 22:51.208
JUST DIDN'T.

23:03.500 --> 23:05.041
WORTHINGTON IS
WHAT YOU WANT, RIGHT?

23:07.041 --> 23:08.625
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT I WANT, DAWSON.

23:08.625 --> 23:10.125
YES OR NO?

23:12.375 --> 23:12.583
YES.

23:18.291 --> 23:20.250
THEN I WANT YOU TO HAVE
MR. BROOKS' MONEY.

23:22.375 --> 23:24.000
DAWSON, ARE YOU INSANE?

23:24.000 --> 23:25.291
I CAN'T--

23:25.291 --> 23:26.875
AT LEAST ENOUGH
TO GET YOU TO SCHOOL.

23:26.875 --> 23:27.917
I KNOW IT SOUNDS CRAZY--

23:27.917 --> 23:29.583
IT'S BEYOND CRAZY.
I MEAN, I APPRECIATE IT,

23:29.583 --> 23:35.458
BUT MR. BROOKS GAVE YOU
THAT MONEY FOR A REASON.

23:35.458 --> 23:36.708
YEAH, HE GAVE ME THAT MONEY
TO DO SOMETHING GREAT,

23:36.708 --> 23:38.208
AND GIVING IT TO YOU
WOULD BE EXACTLY THAT.

23:38.208 --> 23:39.333
I--[LAUGHS]

23:39.333 --> 23:40.625
LOOK, I KNOW
YOU'RE GONNA SAY NO,

23:40.625 --> 23:41.917
AND THAT'S FINE,

23:41.917 --> 23:44.250
BUT DON'T SAY NO
UNTIL YOU'VE AT LEAST

23:44.250 --> 23:45.500
CONSIDERED
THE POSSIBILITY.

23:45.500 --> 23:48.208
JOEY, THIS IS
YOUR ENTIRE FUTURE
WE'RE TALKING ABOUT.

23:48.208 --> 23:49.625
TAKE A DAY,
TAKE LONGER THAN A DAY,

23:49.625 --> 23:52.583
TAKE WHATEVER YOU NEED,
BUT PROMISE ME

23:52.583 --> 23:54.166
THAT YOU WILL
CONSIDER IT.

24:26.000 --> 24:28.583
THERE ARE
NO PICTURES
OF US IN HERE.

24:28.583 --> 24:29.750
HAVE TO DO SOMETHING
ABOUT THAT.

24:32.875 --> 24:34.166
YEAH.

24:35.500 --> 24:37.291
SO I THOUGHT
ABOUT IT, DAWSON.

24:37.291 --> 24:38.250
I REALLY DID.

24:38.250 --> 24:39.750
AND WHAT DID
YOU DECIDE?

24:39.750 --> 24:41.125
I'D NEVER BE ABLE
TO PAY YOU BACK.

24:42.125 --> 24:42.625
WOULDN'T HAVE TO.

24:42.625 --> 24:44.208
DAWSON, I WOULD.

24:44.208 --> 24:46.458
AND I CAN'T TAKE
THAT MUCH MONEY FROM YOU.

24:46.458 --> 24:47.667
I MEAN, EVEN IF IT WERE
HUNDREDS INSTEAD OF THOUSANDS,

24:47.667 --> 24:52.083
JUST EVEN SAYING IT
MAKES IT SOUND LIKE--

24:52.083 --> 24:52.792
LIKE IT WOULD RUIN
OUR FRIENDSHIP?

24:55.041 --> 24:56.708
YEAH.

24:56.708 --> 25:00.000
JOEY, IF OUR
FRIENDSHIP CAN
SURVIVE LAST SUMMER,

25:00.000 --> 25:01.458
IT CAN
SURVIVE ANYTHING.

25:02.000 --> 25:03.083
NOT THIS.

25:03.083 --> 25:05.250
I CAN'T DO THIS.

25:05.667 --> 25:07.667
[SIGHING]

25:07.667 --> 25:08.750
JOEY, STOP. WAIT.

25:11.000 --> 25:13.625
LOOK, I KNOW HOW MUCH
GOING TO THIS SCHOOL
MEANS TO YOU.

25:13.625 --> 25:14.458
I DON'T WANT
YOU TO THROW AWAY
THIS OPPORTUNITY.

25:14.458 --> 25:16.500
DAWSON,
IT'S TOO MUCH.

25:16.500 --> 25:18.250
CAN'T YOU
UNDERSTAND THAT?

25:18.250 --> 25:19.875
NO.

25:19.875 --> 25:23.708
I CAN'T--I CAN'T
UNDERSTAND WHY YOU JUST
WON'T LET ME HELP YOU, JO.

25:23.708 --> 25:26.291
I MEAN, MAYBE I'M BEING
NAIVE HERE, BUT WE'VE ALWAYS
BEEN THERE FOR EACH OTHER.

